## Description {#details}

Provides info so a possible vectorization of a function can be computed.

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a> &#39;VectorFnName&#39; is equivalent to &#39;ScalarFnName&#39; vectorized by a factor &#39;<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/vectorizationfactor">VectorizationFactor</a>&#39;. The VABIPrefix string holds information about isa, mask, vlen, and vparams so a scalar-to-vector mapping of the form: <em>ZGV&lt;isa&gt;&lt;mask&gt;&lt;vlen&gt;&lt;vparams&gt;</em>&lt;scalarname&gt;(&lt;vectorname&gt;) can be constructed where:

&lt;isa&gt; = &quot;&#95;LLVM&#95;&quot; &lt;mask&gt; = &quot;M&quot; if masked, &quot;N&quot; if no mask. &lt;vlen&gt; = Number of concurrent lanes, stored in the <code><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/vectorizationfactor">VectorizationFactor</a></code> field of the <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vecdesc">VecDesc</a></code> struct. If the number of lanes is scalable then &#39;x&#39; is printed instead. &lt;vparams&gt; = &quot;v&quot;, as many as are the numArgs. &lt;scalarname&gt; = the name of the scalar function. &lt;vectorname&gt; = the name of the vector function.

Definition at line 42 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/targetlibraryinfo-h">TargetLibraryInfo.h</a>.
